        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:2:3:132:1",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/132/1",
        "text": [
          " «كَانَ أَبِي عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ يَنْزِلُ اَلْأَبْطَحَ قَلِيلاً ثُمَّ يَدْخُلُ اَلْبُيُوتَ مِنْ غَيْرِ أَنْ يَنَامَ بِالْأَبْطَحِ » فَقُلْتُ لَهُ أَ رَأَيْتَ مَنْ «تَعَجَّلَ فِي يَوْمَيْنِ » عَلَيْهِ أَنْ يُحَصِّبَ قَالَ «لاَ»."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.3027 - Aban narrated from Abu Maryam, from Abu Abdullah (as), that he was asked about al-Hasba (staying at al-Abtah after completing the rites of Hajj).\nImam (as) replied: \"My father (as) would stop briefly at al-Abtah, then enter the houses without sleeping there.\"\nI asked him: \"What about someone who hastened in two days—is it required for him to stay at al-Abtah?\"\nImam (as) replied: \"No.\""
          ]
        }
      },
      {
